.TH "vmw_create_bo_proxy" 9 "vmw_create_bo_proxy" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_create_bo_proxy \- create a proxy surface for the buffer object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_create_bo_proxy
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_mode_fb_cmd2 *mode_cmd "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_buffer_object *bo_mob "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_surface **srf_out "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "mode_cmd" 12
parameters for the new surface
.IP "bo_mob" 12
MOB backing the buffer object
.IP "srf_out" 12
newly created surface
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
When the content FB is a buffer object, we create a surface as a proxy to the
same buffer.  This way we can do a surface copy rather than a surface DMA.
This is a more efficient approach
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, error code otherwise
